@node Introduction "ClipWizard V1.1 - Introduction"
ClipWizard is a commodity that waits for the clipboard contents to change.
When it's changed, it scans the @{"matchfile" LINK Matchfile}, and if it finds a string
that matches the clipboard contents, it executes the command line specified
in the matchfile. The executed program can do many things (see
@{"Example Scripts" LINK ExampleScripts}), eg. join the clipboard contents to your own notebook,
dial a number with your modem or even take an ftp-connection and download
the latest version of ClipWizard :).

See @{"Features" LINK Features} for a complete list of features.
@endnode
